    />

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-8"><h2>Why Deliverability decides whether SMS scales or collapses</h2><p>Shopify merchants treat deliverability as a checkbox until a complaint spike, carrier block, or Black Friday bill forces attention. On shopifysmsapps.com every guide assumes SMS is a regulated, metered channel — not a promotional shortcut.</p><p>Postscript and Attentive lead on enterprise SMS governance; Omnisend and Klaviyo bundle SMS with email when one team owns both channels. Sequenzy does not replace a dedicated SMS sender — it owns lifecycle email beside Postscript so education and winback arcs do not get crammed into 160 characters.</p><p>Run this playbook before scaling broadcasts: document opt-in sources, configure quiet hours by timezone, cap messages per subscriber per week, and model cost per delivered message including discounts. Operators who skip those steps recover revenue in dashboards while burning consent in the real world.</p><p>Implementation week one: audit capture points (checkout, popups, keywords, imports). Week two: launch one high-intent automation with strict exclusions. Week three: add a second flow only if opt-out rate stays below your threshold. Week four: review margin after fees — not gross attributed recovery.</p><p>The failure mode is channel collision: cart SMS and cart email firing within an hour, replenishment texts to gift buyers, launch broadcasts during quiet hours. Build suppression maps in the same doc as your consent architecture and review them before every product drop.</p><p>Measure what protects the list: opt-out rate by flow, reply sentiment, cost per incremental order, complaint rate, and full-price repeat purchase from SMS-acquired buyers. Vanity click metrics hide list damage until the next launch underperforms.</p><p>International SMS adds complexity — US TCPA patterns do not travel unchanged. Segment by country when possible and use platform geo rules before expanding acquisition spend.</p><p>Pair with related guides: TCPA for legal baseline, quiet hours for send windows, email-sms-coordination for stack design, and pricing for message economics. Each page is standalone but the stack only works when combined.</p></div>

    <div class="prose-shopify mb-8"><h2>Operator checklist</h2><p><strong>Step:</strong> Map every opt-in source with screenshot archive and consent timestamp sync to Shopify customer record.</p><p><strong>Step:</strong> Configure quiet hours per timezone before any broadcast — default 8am–9pm local unless category norms differ.</p><p><strong>Step:</strong> Cap automated SMS per subscriber per week; require manual approval for broadcast tiers above the cap.</p><p><strong>Step:</strong> Build cost-per-message spreadsheet: platform fee + carrier fee + average discount per recovered order.</p><p><strong>Step:</strong> Define email-SMS priority rules: which channel sends first on cart recovery, launch, replenishment.</p><p><strong>Step:</strong> Weekly review: opt-outs by flow, reply inbox, suppression collisions, complaint keywords.</p></div>

